Title: Evaluating Dialogue Strategies for Recovering from Misunderstandings  
Author: Masahiro Arakiy, Taro Watanabezand Shuji Doshitaz 
Address: Kyoto 606-01 Japan  
Affiliation: yCenter for Information and Multimedia Studies, Kyoto University,  zDepartment of Information Science, Kyoto University  
Abstract: In spoken dialogue system, misunderstandings yield mainly by recognition error of the system. In order to correct such errors, the recovering methods should be prepared in two stages: the parsing stage and the dialogue stage. In each stage, the dialogue system can employ various recovering methods. In order to examine the performance of the recovering methods under given recognition error rate, we proposed a new evaluation method and examined how the proposed evaluation method suits with measuring the performance.
